<h2>&#128295; SEMAINE 1 — Infrastructure &amp; Capture</h2>

<h3>Supabase Schema</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Créer les migrations SQL (supabase/migrations/)</li>
  <li>Table <strong>users</strong> : id, email, name, role, education_level, bac_series, intent_score, intent_level, last_dwell_minutes, is_booth_registered, parent_email, education_branches</li>
  <li>Table <strong>events</strong> : id, name, city, event_date, venue_id</li>
  <li>Table <strong>schools</strong> : id, name, type, city, user_id, target_fields[], parcoursup, apprenticeship, scholarship_allowed</li>
  <li>Table <strong>formations</strong> : id, school_id, name, level, duration, cost, rncp_code</li>
  <li>Table <strong>scans</strong> : id, user_id, event_id, stand_id, session_id, channel, dwell_estimate, created_at</li>
  <li>Table <strong>matches</strong> : id, student_id, school_id, student_swipe, school_interest</li>
  <li>Table <strong>appointments</strong> : id, student_id, school_id, event_id, slot_time, student_notes, status</li>
  <li>Table <strong>groups</strong> : id, teacher_id, school_name, fair_id, invite_link, invite_link_expiry, member_uids[]</li>
  <li>RLS policies par rôle (student / exhibitor / teacher / admin / service_role)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Score Booth</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Tester POST /api/booth/register end-to-end avec Supabase réel</li>
  <li>Vérifier que le QR généré est scannable par /fair/[id]/scan</li>
  <li>Tester auto-reset countdown 30s kiosque</li>
</ul>

<h3>Auth</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Tester flow register enseignant complet (validation + redirect /teacher/dashboard)</li>
  <li>Tester group-invite/[token] → join group → QR actif</li>
  <li>Vérifier redirect login par rôle (6 rôles)</li>
</ul>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 3 — SEMAINE 2
══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2>&#128295; SEMAINE 2 — Parcours &amp; Scoring</h2>

<h3>QR Scanner caméra</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>app/(student)/fair/[eventId]/scan/page.tsx — intégrer html5-qrcode</li>
  <li>Décoder payload {uid, app} → POST /api/scans channel:entry</li>
  <li>Décoder payload stand {schoolId, type:'school_stand'} → POST /api/scans channel:stand</li>
  <li>Gérer scan de sortie → POST /api/scans channel:exit → dwell_minutes calculé</li>
  <li>Tester flux complet : entrée → stand×3 → sortie → dwell_minutes correct</li>
</ul>

<h3>Intent Score Pipeline</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Vérifier computeIntentScore() produit les bons niveaux (0–39 / 40–69 / 70–100)</li>
  <li>Tester refresh fire-and-forget après chaque scan</li>
  <li>Badge intent sur /profile se met à jour après scan</li>
</ul>

<h3>RDV</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Tester gate : sans scan entrée → message verrouillé visible</li>
  <li>Tester après scan entrée → booking accessible</li>
  <li>Tester annulation RDV → slot libéré pour un autre visiteur</li>
</ul>

<h3>Swipe Deck</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>app/(student)/discover/page.tsx — intégrer react-tinder-card</li>
  <li>Swipe right → INSERT match(student_swipe:'right') → +30 pts intent score</li>
  <li>Swipe left → INSERT match(student_swipe:'left')</li>
</ul>

<h3>Webhook EventMaker</h3>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>app/api/webhooks/eventmaker/route.ts</li>
  <li>Receive POST → lookup email dans table users</li>
  <li>Match exact → lier uid existant au profil EventMaker</li>
  <li>Pas de match → créer profil provisoire + flag needs_review</li>
  <li>Tester avec mock : app/api/mock/eventmaker/route.ts</li>
</ul>

